## Layout

```
{{ project_slug }}/
    .guidelines-ai/      # the conventions — read these before writing code
    .github/             # CI workflow + pull-request template
    .global-hydra/       # shared Hydra config groups: base, optimizer, scheduler
    .vscode/             # editor settings (ruff + ty wiring)
    experiments/         # one dir per experiment: goal.md + a Hydra config.yaml
    packages/            # uv workspace members; the package code lives here
        core/            # the scaffold: contracts, training loop, metrics,
                         #   callbacks, loggers
        dummy-regression/# a synthetic regression task wiring core end to end
    paper/               # the LaTeX article + slides (see paper/README.md)
    ressources/          # catalogued papers + docling conversion (see its README)
    scripts/train.py     # Hydra training launcher, wrapped by `just run`
    justfile             # task runner: just run / check / new / list / paper
    CLAUDE.md            # project overview + index of the guidelines
    prek.toml            # pre-commit hooks (ruff, ty, file hygiene, uv lock)
    ruff.toml            # lint + format rules
    ty.toml              # type-checker config
    pytest.ini           # test config — markers, doctests, importlib mode
    pyproject.toml       # workspace root: dev deps, Python pin
    uv.lock              # resolved lockfile — uv owns it
    .python-version      # interpreter pin (>=3.14)
```

The repo is a uv workspace. The root isn't a package; each subproject lives
under `packages/` with its own `src/` layout and `pyproject.toml`. `core` is the
training scaffold, and `dummy-regression` wires it end to end on a synthetic
task and is the one to copy when starting a new package.

## Getting started

Everything runs through [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) — it owns the
environment and the lockfile, so there's no venv to activate.

```bash
uv run --all-packages pytest              # run the tests and src/ doctests
uv run prek run --all-files               # lint, format, type-check, hygiene checks
just run dummy_regression                 # train the worked-example experiment
```

`--all-packages` makes every workspace member importable; without it uv only
syncs the root. Skip it for commands that don't import package code.

Install the git hooks once so the checks run on every commit:

```bash
uv run prek install
```

## Running an experiment

An experiment lives under `experiments/<name>/`: a `goal.md` stating the
question and a Hydra `config.yaml` wiring the data, model, loss, optimizer, and
eval schedule. The `justfile` drives them:

```bash
just list                     # list experiments
just new my_experiment        # scaffold experiments/my_experiment from the template
just run dummy_regression     # train; append Hydra overrides, e.g. seed=1
just check                    # format, lint, type-check, then the test suite
```

`just run` calls `scripts/train.py`, which instantiates the config and hands the
pieces to `core.fit`. Metrics stream to the terminal and to `.logs/` through the
CSV logger.

## Conventions

The rules for working here live in `.guidelines-ai/` and are loaded by
`CLAUDE.md`. They cover the uv workflow, Python style (typing, docstrings, pure
cores), the PyTorch/einops/jaxtyping modeling conventions, and the commit
format. Read them before adding code.
